      • recreateConsoleHandler

        public void recreateConsoleHandler()
        Checks if the registered handlers contain ConsoleHandler and in case they do, recreates it and replaces for parent logger. This method is necessary as ConsoleHandler captures output stream, what makes logging redirection problematic.
